## Credential Rotation

### When to Rotate

- Monthly (security best practice)
- After staff changes
- If credentials are accidentally exposed
- When switching environments
- After security audits

### Rotation Procedure

1. Generate new credentials in the service
2. Test new credentials in staging environment
3. Update `credentials.md` with new values
4. Deploy to production
5. Revoke old credentials after confirmation
6. Document rotation in audit log

---

## Security Best Practices

✅ **DO:**
- Store credentials in a secure vault (Hashicorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, etc.)
- Use different credentials for each environment
- Rotate credentials regularly (at least monthly)
- Use short-lived tokens when possible
- Enable MFA on service accounts
- Audit credential access logs
- Use environment variables in CI/CD pipelines

❌ **DON'T:**
- Commit credentials to version control
- Share credentials via email or chat
- Store credentials in plain text in logs
- Use the same credentials across environments
- Hardcode credentials in source code
- Share credentials between team members
- Log credential values

